Treasury Secretary Tim Geithner gave a press briefing about the G20 meetings in Pittsburgh. He mentioned that there are signs of optimism about the global recovery, but there is still work to be done. He highlighted the need for countries to shift towards domestic-led growth and to implement stronger financial standards. Geithner also discussed the importance of reforming the framework for cooperation on economic issues to give greater representation to important economies. He mentioned the commitment to reduce carbon emissions and phase out fossil fuel subsidies, which would have positive impacts on national security, health, and economies. Geithner emphasized the need for international cooperation to address the challenges faced by the global economy.